250 g Lean Ground Bison
¾ cup Basmati Rice
0.17 cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Tomato
2 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
7 g Parsley
56 g Almonds, sliced
28 g Sultana Raisins
6 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
2 unit(s) Vegetable Broth Concentrate
15 g Middle Eastern Seasoning
4 g Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend
2 tbsp Butter*
1 tbsp Milk*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water, broth concentrate and Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, stir in rice and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
To a medium bowl, add Middle Eastern Seasoning, bison, half the panko (use all for 4 servings) and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) milk. Season with salt and pepper, then combine.
Roll mixture into 6 (12) equal-sized logs.

On the prepared baking sheet, arrange koftas.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 13-15 min, until golden and cooked through.**

Meanwhile, cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces.
Halve cucumbers lengthwise. Cut into 1/2-inch half-moons.
Roughly chop parsley.
In a large bowl, toss together tomatoes, cucumbers, half the parsley and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil. (TIP: We love the flavour of olive oil here!) Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
When hot, add almonds to the dry pan. Toast for 4-5 min, stirring often, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them, so they don't burn!)
Transfer to a plate.

Fluff rice with a fork, then stir in 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, almonds and raisins. Season with salt.
Divide rice between plates. Top with koftas and cucumber-tomato salad.
Drizzle yogurt sauce over top, then sprinkle with remaining parsley.